        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 3:51PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 351 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated strong thunderstorms along a
line extending from 3 miles northeast of Independence to 5 miles
south of Elk City to 5 miles west of Sedan to 6 miles south of
Dexter. Movement was southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Bigheart...                       Pearsonia...
Wann...                           Wah Sha She State Park...
Webb City...                      South Coffeyville...
Hulah...                          Apperson...
Sunset Lake...                    Foraker...
Grainola...                       Copan...
Shidler...                        Elgin...
Burbank...                        Kaw Lake...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

These storms may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for
northeastern Oklahoma.</instruction>
